parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cold Start Issues with Single Cylinder Operation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cold start issue can cause the motorcycle to stall or run rough, potentially leading to accidents, engine damage, or excess emissions. Running on a single cylinder can also cause mechanical stress and increase the risk of injury.
symptoms: Difficulty starting the motorcycle when cold
stalling
running on a single cylinder
rough engine operation
strong gasoline smell
intermittent misfires
and delayed startup.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature camshaft wear can lead to engine damage, decreased performance, and potentially cause the engine to seize, resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Unexpected wear on the camshaft
despite regular maintenance and use of recommended oil and air filters.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the TFT display can cause the driver to lose access to critical information, such as speed, fuel levels, and ABS control, which can lead to accidents or reduce the driver's ability to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: The TFT display blacks out
the display fails to show speed information
the display fails to show fuel levels
the display fails to show ABS control information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the indicator/blinker control switch can cause the driver to fail to signal intentions, leading to potential accidents or confusion on the road.
symptoms: The indicator/blinker control switch does not engage the blinkers when pushed to the left
the blinkers do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brake lights can cause the vehicle to be less visible to other road users, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate
the brake lights flicker or dim
the ABS system does not engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intake System Defect Causing Valve Wear and Engine Stalling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The manufacturing defect in the intake system can lead to excessive valve wear, engine power loss, and stalling, which can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle stalls in busy intersections, leaving the rider vulnerable to being hit.
symptoms: The motorcycle is hard or impossible to start
stalls frequently
and runs rough on one cylinder
accompanied by an overpowering smell of raw/un-ignited fuel from the exhaust pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issue with fueling or ignition timing can cause the engine to run rough, stall, or fail to start, which can lead to accidents, especially when the vehicle is running on one cylinder or dying, posing a significant safety risk to the rider.
symptoms: The engine takes multiple attempts to start
runs rough on one cylinder
and emits an overpowering smell of raw/un-ignited fuel from the exhaust pipe
especially when using the manufacturer-recommended 91+ octane fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The condensation in the instrument cluster can obstruct the view of critical safety information, such as vehicle speed, traction, and ABS settings, making it difficult or impossible to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: Internal condensation or fogging in the instrument cluster
obscured display
inability to see critical operation/safety information
inability to operate the menu to control settings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The difficulty in starting the engine can lead to safety risks, such as stalling in traffic or losing control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Hard starting
engine dying out
requiring throttle input to keep the engine running
difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cold Start Issues with Rough Idling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The difficulty in starting the motorcycle when cold, along with rough idling, can lead to frustration and potentially cause accidents due to loss of control or stalling in traffic.
symptoms: The motorcycle takes several tries to start when cold
dies several times after starting
idles very rough for several minutes
only runs on one cylinder initially
and takes a minute or so to warm up and return to normal operation.
